Subject: Re: [T2] Clutch cable just broke... Need help

Well, I guess it's more of a divot with a hole in the middle of it. 
It's on the plastic (or metal) collar that fits over the metal clutch 
cable tube.  You can get a rubber cone fitting for your grease gun and 
press it up to the divot and force grease into the tube.

Mike

